import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'].plot(kind='hist', bins=30, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['precipitation'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across all locations?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column=['temp_max', 'temp_min'], by='location', ax=ax)
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary across different locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['wind'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of wind speed over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    weather_count = data.groupby('weather').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    weather_count.plot(kind='bar', x='weather', y='counts', legend=None)
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Condition')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    for i, v in enumerate(weather_count['counts']):
        plt.text(i, v, str(v), ha='center')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
